{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Identifying semantically similar terms has long been a challenge (Chandrasekaran and Mago, 2021), particularly for causal mapping where approaches have included word matching, recommender systems, or thesauri (Giabbanelli and Tawfik, 2019).",
    "PLMs have been successfully used for semantic similarity detection (Peinelt et al., 2020), including in the context of Q&A systems (Al-Besher et al., 2022), hence we leverage this recent advance in our system.",
    "Antonyms form the other equivalence (i.e., words with opposite meanings such as 'unhealthy eating' and 'healthy eating').",
    "We detect them with GPT and integrate them in the map by reversing causal connections (Fig. 4c).",
    "Prompt engineering was necessary to minimize the number of errors made by GPT when identifying equivalent terms."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Identifying semantically similar terms has long been a challenge (Chandrasekaran and Mago, 2021), particularly for causal mapping where approaches have included word matching, recommender systems, or thesauri (Giabbanelli and Tawfik, 2019).",
